{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"913b7e35-44e6-47da-81b6-3137385572f2","content":"Here's how to migrate from `VSTest@3` to Microsoft.Testing.Platform while keeping TRX reports and code coverage:\n\n### 1. Update your test project\n\nAdd these to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### 2. Replace VSTest@3 with DotNetCoreCLI@2\n\nSwap the pipeline task:\n\n```yaml\n# Before (VSTest@3)\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testSelector: 'testAssemblies'\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**\\*Tests.dll'\n    resultsFolder: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)\\TestResults'\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n\n# After (dotnet test with Microsoft.Testing.Platform)\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: 'test'\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration $(BuildConfiguration)\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=testresults.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n```\n\n### 3. Publish results & coverage\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish test results'\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: 'VSTest'\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n  condition: succeededOrFailed()\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### Key differences\n\n| | VSTest@3 | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Runner** | `vstest.console.exe` | Built into test binary |\n| **TRX** | Automatic | `--logger trx` |\n| **Coverage** | `codeCoverageEnabled` | `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` |\n| **Results** | Auto-published | Needs `PublishTestResults@2` |\n\n> **Tip:** If you want Cobertura-format coverage (for richer reports), add the `coverlet.collector` NuGet package and use `--collect \"XPlat Code Coverage\"` instead.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d39000b4-9ac0-4b50-846f-79f623f4f6af","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory appears to be empty. This seems like a general question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps pipelines. Let me provide a helpful answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":678,"requestId":"7C1A:16E90D:24E8AEA:28F5732:69F93EF6"},"id":"6e963a64-6c5a-4395-925e-33d703d9a237","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:51:15.673Z","parentId":"128c0df5-b3ae-4217-b4e7-56e0484cd658"}
